messages.content:
@here
So, I know you guys have been aware of my long absence from the server recently; and well, the main reasons were due to life, interests shifting, and overall boredom to be honest
*However,* I've got something big in the works that'll hopefully make up for that :)
Because you see, months ago, I've been thinking.. More than usual actually; this time about why exactly Rpurg 3 failed.
Well, it was an interesting experiment to say the least, but the public rpurgatory fell apart within days. A bit sad, but looking back, I could understand why!
The main problem was that we tried to directly copy over the Rpurg we had at the time into a public setting, when the server was mainly suited towards a close-knit community/friend group, and while it's worked for a long time.. Slowly, the server passed its better days.
It was then that I realized what we really needed; we needed something new.. Something better than this.
oh?
well this should be interesting

While Rpurg 2 was a step-up from its predecessor, it was still riddled with problems that had yet to be solved.. Such as new people having difficulty fitting in with the current roleplays in bot rp due to not understanding the extensive plot, the complete lack of interest of rping in the dusty and abandoned rp channels, and the very little non-rping aspects of the server, to name a few.
So, why not try revamping it? Why not try breathing new life into rpurg's community once again? But instead of doing it through a system more meant for a small community, we'll do it through something better..!
And that, was when I was struck with an idea. A Project! And I called it.. Project **NewPurg!**
And heres a snippet (and it's current look so far) of what it looks like! It's only the RPing segments for now, but what do you think?
dnd?
Yep!
I'm suprised to learn you'd include dnd into the mix
I assume you know how to play it?
I thought it would be a great idea if we tried expanding a bit into other kinds of rps

And not really, but we could choose other people who actually *do* know how to play dnd if they happen to join that server; Mods don't necessarily have to be the dungeonmaster since it could be anyone! Given they know how to play, of course
I actually explained NewPurg to Seth in the past! But I didn't want to tell you guys yet because I wanted to add more onto this, but I've been struggling with ideas for NewPurg for a while now..
But since several important members of rpurg are back, I thought now would be a good time to finally unveil this to you guys
You don't have to respond to it now since it's pretty late on my end, but let me know what you think!
And if you have any more questions about NewPurg, just leave them here for me to answer later
anyway I gotta go to sleep, hope you guys like this!

revamp rpurg
Well, Newpurg is gonna be geared more towards a community, and not just for a small friend group anymore
The reason why Rpurg 3 failed was because we literally tried to copy over Rpurg 2 for something that was meant for the public, but we had no systems or anything in place to actually *prepare* for one

Rpurg 2 worked best, or at least functionally with a close-knit community, when we need it to be geared towards the public; which means we need clear, more strict rules, less clutter for the channels, and other things to keep people entertained when they're waiting on other people or if they're not interested in roleplay at all
thats why i added in more roleplay types since the server's more public
and its also why im steering Newpurg towards being less dependant on the rp channels, because not everyone's gonna be interested in doing them
